caption: Some good Mexican food here at Huarache. It's one of my fave Mexican joints in this neighborhood. I usually have the tacos. They're affordable and delicious. The green sauce is pretty yummy. They're also served with a smoky hot sauce. Definitely give them a try. Right off the 4 train Mount Eden stop, on the hill.
The service is always quick, excellent vibes, very kind staff members. Will eat here again when I get nearby.

This little known taqueria in the Bronx probably has the best authentic Mexican burritos I've ever tasted, and I'm a bit of a burrito connoisseur. You can order off the menu, but since every burrito is made fresh it's no issue for the chef to take special requests (I like mine extra spicy).  If you're in the area and you want burritos or tacos, I couldn't recommend this place more highly.
